`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Email templates are a legitimate exception to the "no inline styles" rule. HTML email rendering engines (Gmail, Outlook, Apple Mail) operate like IE6-era browsers — they strip `<link>` tags, ignore `<style>` blocks, and only reliably render inline styles. This is why react-email and similar libraries always use inline styles.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

The file already documents this correctly with a `design-lint-ignore` comment. **No changes are needed** — the violations flagged on lines 78–89 are all covered by the existing ignore directive at line 1.

